wkins. WordPress 4.5 has many new interesting features like Inline linking, Live responsive previews, custom logos, smart image resizing and more. You can read more about WordPress 4.5 &#8220;Coleman&#8221; at it official release post. rtCampers [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/core-contribution-wordpress-4-5-rtcampers/\">Core Contribution to WordPress 4.5 by rtCampers</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Aditya Kane\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1925:\"<p>Earlier today, WordPress version 4.5 &#8220;Coleman&#8221; was released. This version is named in honour of the a jazz artist Coleman Hawkins. WordPress 4.5 has many new interesting features like Inline linking, Live responsive previews, custom logos, smart image resizing and more.</p>\n<p>You can read more about WordPress 4.5 &#8220;Coleman&#8221; at it <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/news/2016/04/coleman/\">official release post</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"rtcampers-contributing-to-core\">rtCampers contributing to core</h2>\n<p>With version 4.5, we have 4 rtCampers who made it to the list as contributors!</p>\n<p>Congratulations to Chandrakumar Patel, Juhi Saxena, Ritesh Patel and Utkarsh Patel for contributing code to WordPress core.</p>\n<p>Contributing code to WordPress core has been a practice encouraged at rtCamp for a long time. Along with contributing code, many rtCampers are involved in other ways within the WordPress eco-system.</p>\n<p>You can read about our <a href=\"https://rtcamp.com/wordpress/\">WordPress contributions here</a>.</p>\n<p>Also congratulations to some of our old ex-rtCampers who also are on the contributors list.</p>\n<h2 id=\"compatibility-with-wordpress-44\">Compatibility with WordPress 4.5</h2>\n<p>We have tested our plugins and themes with WordPress 4.5 and they all play well with the new version. In case you have any questions or concerns feel free to raise a <a href=\"https://rtcamp.com/premium-support/\">support ticket for your purchased product</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Link:</strong> <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/news/2016/04/coleman/\">WordPress 4.5 Release Post</a> | <a href=\"https://rtcamp.com/wordpress/\">rtCamp’s WordPress Contributions</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/core-contribution-wordpress-4-5-rtcampers/\">Core Contribution to WordPress 4.5 by rtCampers</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"Our Client Geometric Global Acquired by HCL\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/client-geometric-global-acquired-hcl/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 04 Apr 2016 14:04:21 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"3DPLM\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Acquisition\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Dassault Systèmes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Geometric global\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"HCL\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://rtcamp.com/?p=146514\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:323:\"<p>Our client, Geometric Global, entered into two major deals with HCL and Dassault Systèmes</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/client-geometric-global-acquired-hcl/\">Our Client Geometric Global Acquired by HCL</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Vivek Jain\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2206:\"<p>We are happy to see one of our valuable clients, <a href=\"http://geometricglobal.com/\">Geometric Global</a>, entered into two major deals. <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/72x72/1f642.png\" alt=\"?\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.hcltech.com/\">HCL Tech</a> will acquire Geometric&#8217;s IT services business for Rs 1,283 crore ($200 million) in an all-share deal.</li>\n<li>Geometric also agreed to offload its 3DPLM ownership to Dassault Systèmes for Rs 441 crore.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Below is excerpt from the media release that Geometric Global published on its website.</p>\n<blockquote><p>MUMBAI, India. April 01, 2016: Geometric Ltd (Geometric) is pleased to announce the transfer of its business to HCL Technologies Ltd (HCL Tech). Under the transaction, the entire business of Geometric Ltd will be transferred to HCL Tech by way of demerger, except for its 58% share in the joint venture with Dassault Systèmes (3DS) (3DPLM Software Solutions Limited (3DPLM)). In return, shareholders of Geometric Ltd will receive shares in HCL Tech in a swap ratio of 10 equity shares of HCL Tech for every 43 equity shares of Geometric Ltd.</p></blockquote>\n<p>As per <a href=\"http://profit.ndtv.com/news/market/article-hcl-techs-rs-1-283-crore-deal-sends-geometric-to-52-week-high-1334118\">media reports</a>, Geometric shares surged nearly 20% to hit a 52-week high today as investors reacted positively.</p>\n<p>Being Geometric Global&#8217;s web technology partner, rtCamp has witnessed hard work that they put for their products and customers. We wish them luck for exciting  journey ahead.</p>\n<p><strong>Links:</strong> <a href=\"http://geometricglobal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Final-Geometric_Media_Release_HCL_April_01_2016.pdf\">Geometric Global</a> | <a href=\"http://www.hcltech.com/press-releases/engineering-and-rd-services/hcl-technologies-signs-definitive-agreement-acquire\">HCL Tech</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/client-geometric-global-acquired-hcl/\">Our Client Geometric Global Acquired by HCL</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"rtCampers visited WordCamp Mumbai 2016\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/wordcamp-mumbai-2016/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 28 Mar 2016 11:43:20 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Events\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"2016\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Mumbai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"WordCamp\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://rtcamp.com/?p=145134\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:312:\"<p>rtCamp\'s WordCamp Mumbai 2016 experience and slides from Scaling WooCommerce session by Rahul Bansal</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/wordcamp-mumbai-2016/\">rtCampers visited WordCamp Mumbai 2016</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Aditya Kane\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4147:\"<p>Over the weekend, many rtCampers attended WordCamp Mumbai 2016. Every WordCamp is unique and fun and this one was no different.</p>\n<p>WordCamp Mumbai had many interesting speakers and one of them was Rahul, our CEO. He spoke on &#8220;<a href=\"https://2016.mumbai.wordcamp.org/session/scaling-woocommerce-for-high-transaction-stores/\">Scaling WooCommerce for high transaction stores</a>&#8220;.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-146014\" src=\"https://cdn.rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/rahul-wcmumbai.jpg\" alt=\"rahul-wcmumbai\" width=\"518\" height=\"345\" srcset=\"https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/rahul-wcmumbai.jpg 518w, https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/rahul-wcmumbai-400x266.jpg 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 518px) 100vw, 518px\" /></p>\n<p>Below are his slides from the talk and link to <a href=\"http://rt.cx/wcwst\">Window Shopping Technique codes</a>.</p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/key/sVtw7GBEpSWUHE\" width=\"427\" height=\"356\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" style=\"border:1px solid #CCC; border-width:1px; margin-bottom:5px; max-width: 100%;\" allowfullscreen> </iframe>\n<div style=\"margin-bottom:5px\"> <strong> <a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/rtcamp/scaling-woocommerce-wordcamp-mumbai-2016\" title=\"Scaling WooCommerce - WordCamp Mumbai 2016\" target=\"_blank\">Scaling WooCommerce &#8211; WordCamp Mumbai 2016</a> </strong> from <strong><a href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/rtcamp\" target=\"_blank\">rtCamp </a></strong> </div>\n<h2>Getting involved!</h2>\n<p>WordCamp Mumbai 2016 had your&#8217;s truly as a co-organiser, we had Rahul Bansal the CEO as a speaker and as a company we also loved being sponsors at the event.</p>\n<p>As sponsors we had a nice desk where we could speak to people interested in the WordPress ecosystem and opportunities in India.</p>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Come and say hello to us <a href=\"https://twitter.com/WCMumbai\">@WCMumbai</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/kY3gYVwykI\">pic.twitter.com/kY3gYVwykI</a></p>\n<p>&mdash; Vivek Jain (@svivekjain) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/svivekjain/status/708506377082290176\">March 12, 2016</a></p></blockquote>\n<p><script async src=\"//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></p>\n<p>Rahul&#8217;s son Raj, was probably the youngest attendee at WordCamp Mumbai ever. He is less than two but he was really a lot less cranky and more attentive than many grownups.</p>\n<p><img class=\"size-large wp-image-146013 alignnone\" src=\"https://cdn.rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/raj-youngest-wordcamper-720x479.jpg\" alt=\"raj-youngest-wordcamper\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" srcset=\"https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/raj-youngest-wordcamper-720x479.jpg 720w, https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/raj-youngest-wordcamper-400x266.jpg 400w, https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/raj-youngest-wordcamper-768x511.jpg 768w, https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/raj-youngest-wordcamper.jpg 1125w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" /></p>\n<p>At the selfie booth, some rtCampers let their hair down and had posed for some fun pics.</p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_146010\" style=\"width: 518px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img class=\"wp-image-146010 size-full\" src=\"https://cdn.rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/pradeep-nitun-selfie.jpg\" alt=\"pradeep-nitun-selfie\" width=\"518\" height=\"345\" srcset=\"https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/pradeep-nitun-selfie.jpg 518w, https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/pradeep-nitun-selfie-400x266.jpg 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 518px) 100vw, 518px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Pradeep Sonawane and Nitun Lanjewar</figcaption></figure>\n<p>Want to join this fun group of individuals who eat, drink and breathe WordPress? Check out our job openings at <a href=\"http://careers.rtcamp.com\">Careers @ rtCamp</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/wordcamp-mumbai-2016/\">rtCampers visited WordCamp Mumbai 2016</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"Wapuu on our minds at rtCamp\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/the-wapuu-effect-at-rtcamp/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 23 Mar 2016 14:00:23 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://rtcamp.com/?p=145626\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:314:\"<p>After WordCamp Mumbai 2016, the popular mascot \"Wapuu\" inspired rtCampers to come up with newer versions. </p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/the-wapuu-effect-at-rtcamp/\">Wapuu on our minds at rtCamp</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Aditya Kane\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3450:\"<p>Last week many rtCampers attended WordCamp Mumbai 2016. The event had a lot of WordPress awesomeness to take in but after <a href=\"https://twitter.com/naokomc\">Naoko Takano</a>&#8216;s introduction of the Wapuu mascot during her talk, had many rtCampers come back home to Pune with &#8216;Wapuu&#8217; on our minds.</p>\n<p>&#8220;Wapuu&#8221; is the mascot of WordPress community in Japan. It was created to promoted WordPress in Japan and like the software the mascot is also GPL v2. This means there are several derivatives of the Wapuu mascot, made by many for their WordCamps or community. You can read more of its <a href=\"http://wapuu.jp/2015/12/12/wapuu-origins/\">origins story here</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/ganeshkerkar\">Ganesh Kerkar</a> who heads our design team tried his hand at creating a &#8220;Wapuu&#8221;. He came up with <strong>&#8220;Bapuu&#8221;. </strong>I think it is first Indian contribution to the <a href=\"http://jawordpressorg.github.io/wapuu/\">Wapuu archives</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-145627 size-full\" src=\"https://cdn.rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/bapuu-wapuu.png\" alt=\"bapuu-wapuu\" width=\"300\" height=\"330\" /></p>\n<p>While Ganesh was busy coming up with new Wapuu versions, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/actual_saurabh\">Saurabh Shukla</a> who freelances for us as a WordPress trainer and hangs out most days at our office in Pune, also came up with some creative new Wapuu versions.</p>\n<p><strong>Wapuu ji Chaudhary </strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-145629\" src=\"https://cdn.rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wapuu-ji-chaudhary.png\" alt=\"wapuu-ji-chaudhary\" width=\"300\" height=\"330\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Shikari Wapuu</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-145630\" src=\"https://cdn.rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/shikari-wapuu.png\" alt=\"shikari-wapuu\" width=\"273\" height=\"330\" /></p>\n<p>and another one that says <strong>&#8220;Save the Tiger&#8221;</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-145628\" src=\"https://cdn.rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wapuu-tiger.png\" alt=\"wapuu-tiger\" width=\"299\" height=\"330\" /></p>\n<p>Last but not the least, coming back to Ganesh&#8217;s latest contribution &#8211; we now we have a <strong>rtCamp Wapuu or &#8220;R2&#8221;</strong> &#8211; which seems to have stuck on as it&#8217;s nickname.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-145631\" src=\"https://cdn.rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/r2-wapuu.png\" alt=\"r2-wapuu\" width=\"300\" height=\"330\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>I am sure a lot more Indianised versions of Wapuu will show up in the future. You can look up all the Wapuu versions on its archive page. If you are a designer and want to contribute one, you can send a pull request on <a href=\"https://github.com/jawordpressorg/wapuu/\">Github</a>.</p>\n<p>Keep track of more Indianised versions of Wapuu, we will posting them on our <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ganeshkerkar\">Twitter feed</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Links: </strong><a href=\"http://jawordpressorg.github.io/wapuu/\">Wapuu Archive</a> | <a href=\"http://wapuu.jp/2015/12/12/wapuu-origins/\">Wapuu Origins</a> | <a href=\"https://github.com/jawordpressorg/wapuu/\">Github</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/the-wapuu-effect-at-rtcamp/\">Wapuu on our minds at rtCamp</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:44:\"Catch up with an rtCamper at WordCamp Mumbai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/catch-up-with-an-rtcamper-at-wordcamp-mumbai/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 11 Mar 2016 13:33:52 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Events\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"WordCamp Mumbai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://rtcamp.com/?p=144944\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:566:\"<p>Tomorrow begins WordCamp Mumbai 2016. Even though rtCamp is based in Pune, we have had very fond memories of previous WordCamps in Mumbai. Rahul has been a speaker in 2014 and 2015. He is speaking again this year about Scaling WooCommerce. Yours truly, has been a co-organiser for 3 years in a row. It&#8217;s most [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/catch-up-with-an-rtcamper-at-wordcamp-mumbai/\">Catch up with an rtCamper at WordCamp Mumbai</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Aditya Kane\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3411:\"<p>Tomorrow begins <a href=\"https://2016.mumbai.wordcamp.org/\">WordCamp Mumbai 2016</a>. Even though rtCamp is based in Pune, we have had very fond memories of previous WordCamps in Mumbai.</p>\n<p>Rahul has been a speaker in 2014 and 2015. He is speaking again this year about <a href=\"https://2016.mumbai.wordcamp.org/scale-woocommerce-with-rahul-bansal/\">Scaling WooCommerce</a>. Yours truly, has been a co-organiser for 3 years in a row. It&#8217;s most probably my last year as an organiser as, I recently moved to Pune.</p>\n<p>We have also proudly sponsored WordCamp Mumbai for the second year in a row. <a href=\"https://2016.mumbai.wordcamp.org/scale-woocommerce-with-rahul-bansal/\">This year as Silver sponsors</a> we will be lucky to have a table at the venue.  So if you are attending WordCamp Mumbai, drop in at our table and say &#8216;hello&#8217;. Or just catch up with any rtCamper and ask us more about what we do around WordPress.</p>\n<p>You will catch them wearing a rtCamp t-shirt usually.</p>\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-version=\"7\" style=\" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:640px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);\"><div style=\"padding:8px;\">\n<div style=\" background:#F8F8F8; line-height:0; margin-top:40px; padding:41.7052826691% 0; text-align:center; width:100%;\">\n<div style=\" background:url(data:image/png;base64,); display:block; height:44px; margin:0 auto -44px; position:relative; top:-22px; width:44px;\"></div>\n</div>\n<p style=\" margin:8px 0 0 0; padding:0 4px;\"> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/BCz9hakMwnW/\" style=\" color:#000; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none; word-wrap:break-word;\" target=\"_blank\">We had to share this Happy Selfie that @immilind clicked wearing rtCamp t-shirts. See you at #WordCampMumbai !</a></p>\n<p style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;\">A photo posted by rtCamp (@rtcamp) on <time style=\" font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px;\" datetime=\"2016-03-11T11:57:53+00:00\">Mar 11, 2016 at 3:57am PST</time></p>\n</div>\n</blockquote>\n<p><script async defer src=\"//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js\"></script></p>\n<p>We are hiring! So do not feel shy to ask about job opportunities at rtCamp. You can also check out <a href=\"https://careers.rtcamp.com/\">Careers @ rtCamp</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/catch-up-with-an-rtcamper-at-wordcamp-mumbai/\">Catch up with an rtCamper at WordCamp Mumbai</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"rtBiz.io – A new home for our rtBiz Project!\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/rtbiz-new-home/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 10 Feb 2016 14:14:48 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"rtbiz\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://rtcamp.com/?p=143006\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:353:\"<p>Our rtBiz project has moved to a new home - rtbiz.io. The new website will be dedicated to the updates and store for the rtBiz project.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/rtbiz-new-home/\">rtBiz.io &#8211; A new home for our rtBiz Project!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Aditya Kane\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1355:\"<p>A few months ago, we brain stormed how best can be serve our product users and our clients. The solution was simple yet complicated. What we settled on was to create separate websites for some of our projects.</p>\n<p>We think it will make things easy for users and for us. A few days ago, we migrated rtBiz related content and store to <a href=\"https://rtBiz.io\">rtBiz.io</a>. The new domain will have content, updates and details exclusive to our rtBiz project.</p>\n<p>You can purchase <a href=\"https://rtbiz.io/helpdesk/\">rtBiz Helpdesk</a> &#8211; a really nice cool ticketing support plugin that integrates well with Easy Digital Downloads and WooCommerce. The plugin is available for $39.00 <em>(US).</em></p>\n<h2>What changes for our customers?</h2>\n<p>Our store for selling rtBiz Helpdesk has moved from rtCamp.com to rtBiz.io. Your license will remain active as is and we have moved all our customers to the new website.</p>\n<p>As a customer if you have questions, do let us know by raising a <a href=\"https://rtbiz.io/premium-support/\">support ticket</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Link:</strong> <a href=\"https://rtBiz.io\">rtBiz.io</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/rtbiz-new-home/\">rtBiz.io &#8211; A new home for our rtBiz Project!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"Let’s Catch Up at PressNomics4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/pressnomics-4-catch-up/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 04 Feb 2016 14:02:18 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"conference\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"PressNomics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://rtcamp.com/?p=141890\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:354:\"<p>PressNomics is a conference for those that power the WordPress Economy. rtCamp is attending the conference this year and also a community sponsor.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/pressnomics-4-catch-up/\">Let’s Catch Up at PressNomics4</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Rahul Bansal\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2088:\"<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-142358\" src=\"https://cdn.rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/pn4-720x276.png\" alt=\"pn4\" width=\"640\" height=\"245\" srcset=\"https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/pn4-720x276.png 720w, https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/pn4-400x153.png 400w, https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/pn4-768x294.png 768w, https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/pn4.png 960w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" />PressNomics is, as it describes itself &#8220;The conference for those that power the WordPress Economy&#8221;.</p>\n<p>As rtCamp is part of WordPress economy, we decided to attend the conference this year and felt that it was also important to be a sponsor in some way.</p>\n<p>We are proud to be community sponsors for <a href=\"http://pressnomics.com/\">PressNomics</a>.</p>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Please welcome <a href=\"https://twitter.com/rtCamp\">@rtcamp</a> as a Community-Level sponsor. (wicked great nginx configs for WP) <a href=\"https://t.co/TUzx7JFwII\">pic.twitter.com/TUzx7JFwII</a></p>\n<p>&mdash; PressNomics (@PressNomics) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/PressNomics/status/693130892340912128\">January 29, 2016</a></p></blockquote>\n<p><script async src=\"//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></p>\n<p>Since I am attending PressNomics4, I would love to meet up with fellow community members. If you want to have a word, discuss building a WordPress based agency in India, I would love being part of such discussions.</p>\n<p>You can simply tweet me <a href=\"https://twitter.com/rahul286\">@rahul286</a> to catchup or leave a comment on this blog post. The best way to recognise me would be look out for a guy wearing a t-shirt with rtCamp logo.</p>\n<p><strong>Link:</strong> <a href=\"http://pressnomics.com/\">PressNomics</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/pressnomics-4-catch-up/\">Let’s Catch Up at PressNomics4</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"Wufoo to Gravity Forms importer WordPress plugin is now Free!\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/migrate-wufoo-form-gravity-form-free/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 02 Feb 2016 14:12:02 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://rtcamp.com/?p=140646\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:401:\"<p>We are making our Wufoo to Gravity Forms WordPress plugin free. We are releasing the code on Github and it is also available on WordPress plugin repo.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/migrate-wufoo-form-gravity-form-free/\">Wufoo to Gravity Forms importer WordPress plugin is now Free!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Nitun Lanjewar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1734:\"<p>Few years ago we released <a href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/wufoo-to-gravity-forms-importer/\">Wufoo to Gravity content importer plugin</a>. We got a good response from users in terms of enhancements to add and also feedback.</p>\n<p>We are organising our list of premium plugins and felt that there were many who wanted to migrate their Wufoo form data to Gravity Forms. It would be better to actually offer this plugin as a free plugin back to the community.</p>\n<p>You can now download use this plugin from the official <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/migrate-wufoo-to-gravity-forms/\">WordPress plugin directory</a>.</p>\n<p>The plugin&#8217;s code can be found on <a href=\"https://github.com/rtCamp/migrate-wufoo-to-gravity-forms\">Github</a>. If you want to report any issues or need to make changes, feel free to send us a pull request.</p>\n<p>If you have already purchased this plugin from our store, you can use our <a href=\"https://rtcamp.com/premium-support/\">premium support</a>  if you need any assistance.</p>\n<p>Your plugin license key is valid for one year as mentioned <a href=\"http://docs.rtcamp.com/license/\">license key</a> will not restrict any feature of the plugin, it was just used to give future updates and premium support.</p>\n<p><strong>Links</strong>: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/migrate-wufoo-to-gravity-forms/\">Wufoo to Gravity content importer plugin</a> | <a href=\"https://github.com/rtCamp/migrate-wufoo-to-gravity-forms\">Github</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/migrate-wufoo-form-gravity-form-free/\">Wufoo to Gravity Forms importer WordPress plugin is now Free!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"Shmart Payment Gateway Addon for Easy Digital Downloads is Free\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/shmart-addon-easy-digital-downloads-free/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 21 Jan 2016 14:47:17 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://rtcamp.com/?p=140643\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:443:\"<p>The Shmart Payment Gateway Addon for Easy Digital Downloads allows using Shmart payment gateway with your EasyDigitalDownload store and is now part of the official WordPress plugin repo.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/shmart-addon-easy-digital-downloads-free/\">Shmart Payment Gateway Addon for Easy Digital Downloads is Free</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Aditya Kane\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1647:\"<p>Few months ago we introduced <a href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/shmart-payment-gateway-easy-digital-downloads-plugin/\">Shmart Payment Gateway addon</a> for Easy Digital Downloads plugin. This plugin add-on was mainly developed by us for our <a href=\"https://rtcamp.com/products/\">store</a> that runs on Easy Digital Downloads. We are streamlining our product line and decided to make some of our premium plugins available free.</p>\n<h2>What is Shmart?</h2>\n<p>It is a payment gateway that is very popular in India.  <a href=\"http://shmart.in/\">Shmart Payment Gateway</a> allows users to purchase the product in Indian currency (INR). It also accepts payments via all VISA and MasterCard debit and credit cards and internet banking of 27 major banks and IMPS payment option with over 55 banks.</p>\n<p>This add-on that allows using Shmart payment gateway with your EasyDigitalDownload store is now part of the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/payment-gateway-easy-digital-downloads-shmart/\">official WordPress plugin repo</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Links: </strong><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/payment-gateway-easy-digital-downloads-shmart/\">Shmart Payment Gateway for EDD Addon</a> | <a href=\"https://github.com/rtCamp/payment-gateway-easydigitaldownloads-shmart\">Github</a> | <a href=\"https://github.com/rtCamp/payment-gateway-easydigitaldownloads-shmart/wiki\">Documentation</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/shmart-addon-easy-digital-downloads-free/\">Shmart Payment Gateway Addon for Easy Digital Downloads is Free</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:29:\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";a:16:{s:6:\"server\";s:5:\"nginx\";s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Tue, 07 Jun 2016 07:49